&lt;Quotron Systems Inc> said it signeda contract to deliver financial information services to morethan 500 Merrill Lynch Pierce Fenner and Smith offices.    The agreement provides all the offices served by Quotron beextended through November 1989, and gives Merrill Lynch theoption to extend the contract through February 1993, thecompany said.    The cost of the contract was not disclosed.    Quotron is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Citicorp &lt;CCI>, andis not traded publicly. Reuter&#3;